  "prompt": "Can anyone top ten thriller movies of all time?",
  "response": "Here\u2019s a list of ten highly acclaimed thriller movies that are often considered among the best of all time. Note that rankings can be subjective, and this list is not definitive:\n\n1. **Psycho (1960)**\n   - Directed by Alfred Hitchcock, this film is a seminal work in the thriller and horror genres, known for its shocking plot twists and iconic shower scene.\n\n2. **The Silence of the Lambs (1991)**\n   - Directed by Jonathan Demme, this film won five Academy Awards, including Best Picture, and features unforgettable performances by Jodie Foster and Anthony Hopkins.\n\n3. **Se7en (1995)**\n   - Directed by David Fincher, this dark and gritty film follows two detectives tracking a serial killer who uses the seven deadly sins as his motives.\n\n4. **The Sixth Sense (1999)**\n   - Directed by M. Night Shyamalan, this film is known for its twist ending and moving performances, especially by young Haley Joel Osment.\n\n5. **Rear Window (1954)**\n   - Another Hitchcock classic, this film centers on a photographer who believes he has witnessed a murder from his apartment window.\n\n6. **North by Northwest (1959)**\n   - Directed by Alfred Hitchcock, this film is a quintessential thriller with iconic scenes like the crop duster chase and the climax at Mount Rushmore.\n\n7. **The Usual Suspects (1995)**\n   - Directed by Bryan Singer, this film is famous for its complex plot and the shocking revelation about the elusive criminal Keyser S\u00f6ze.\n\n8. **Gone Girl (2014)**\n   - Directed by David Fincher, this film is a gripping adaptation of Gillian Flynn's novel, featuring stellar performances by Ben Affleck and Rosamund Pike.\n\n9. **Zodiac (2007)**\n   - Directed by David Fincher, this film delves into the hunt for the Zodiac Killer and is praised for its meticulous attention to detail and atmospheric tension.\n\n10. **Memento (2000)**\n    - Directed by Christopher Nolan, this innovative film tells its story backwards and follows a man with short-term memory loss trying to solve his wife's murder.\n\nThese films have been selected based on their critical acclaim, influence on the genre, and their ability to keep audiences on the edge of their seats.",
